WEBVTT

00:00.931 --> 00:03.313
[ pop music playing ]

00:08.007 --> 00:09.733
EXCUSE ME,
SORRY SORRY.

00:09.801 --> 00:11.182
CUTE BABY.

00:12.426 --> 00:14.428
Man on radio: Attention Boston baseball fans,

00:14.496 --> 00:16.326
if you forgot to check
Twitter this morning,

00:16.394 --> 00:18.603
you might want to head on down  to Boston Pediatric Hospital's

00:18.672 --> 00:20.295
charity blood drive.
Why?

00:20.364 --> 00:22.228
Well, they've just
tweeted a contest:

00:22.297 --> 00:25.748
the first 500 donors
get to meet celebrity host
Richie Miranda!

00:25.818 --> 00:27.405
- [ woman moans ]
- [ man laughs ]

00:27.475 --> 00:29.097
Man:
Alexis, control yourself.

00:29.167 --> 00:30.684
Alexis:
I'm sorry, but who
doesn't love them

00:30.754 --> 00:32.686
- a little Richie Miranda?
- Man: Uh, police officers,

00:32.756 --> 00:34.619
- drug counselors maybe.
- Awww.

00:34.689 --> 00:36.450
Man:
I mean, the guy may be
an All-Star ballplayer,

00:36.518 --> 00:38.314
but he still got busted
for drug possession.

00:38.383 --> 00:40.454
If you still love him,
go to that blood drive!

00:40.523 --> 00:42.283
Maybe he'll give you
an autograph, but hurry.

00:42.351 --> 00:44.630
I hear there's already
a pretty big line.

00:45.561 --> 00:48.771
♪ AS A WAY THEY COULD
STEAL YOU FROM ME ♪

00:48.841 --> 00:52.292
♪ YOU'VE BEEN DOWN,
DOWN FOR DAYS AND DAYS ♪

00:52.362 --> 00:55.469
♪ BUT SEARCHING FOR ANOTHER
WON'T FIX A THING ♪

00:55.537 --> 00:58.713
♪ YOU'VE BEEN DOWN,
DOWN FOR DAYS AND DAYS ♪

00:58.781 --> 01:00.439
♪ BUT SEARCHING
FOR ANOTHER... ♪

01:00.508 --> 01:01.853
MATT FRITZ FROM
THE "BOSTON SENTINEL"--

01:01.923 --> 01:03.786
NO PRESS TODAY, SIR.
THIS IS A CHARITY EVENT.

01:03.856 --> 01:05.823
YOU'RE WELCOME TO GIVE BLOOD,
BUT YOU GOTTA WAIT YOUR TURN.

01:05.893 --> 01:09.379
♪ NOTHING'S GOING TO CHANGE
UNTIL YOU LOOK INSIDE ♪

01:09.448 --> 01:12.658
♪ NO, NOTHING'S GOING
TO CHANGE UNTIL YOU
LOOK INSIDE ♪

01:12.727 --> 01:16.248
♪ YOU'VE BEEN DOWN,
DOWN FOR DAYS AND DAYS ♪

01:16.317 --> 01:19.286
♪ BUT SEARCHING FOR ANOTHER
WON'T FIX A THING ♪

01:19.355 --> 01:21.390
♪ YOU'VE BEEN DOWN... ♪

01:21.460 --> 01:22.875
EXCUSE ME,
DO I KNOW YOU?

01:22.944 --> 01:24.843
UH, YEAH! I'M...

01:24.912 --> 01:26.671
OH-HAY-J--

01:26.740 --> 01:28.536
OJEALO'S FROM NIGERIA.

01:31.676 --> 01:33.575
YEAH.

01:53.698 --> 01:55.424
[ knocks ]

01:56.944 --> 01:58.359
APRIL.

02:00.361 --> 02:02.362
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

02:02.432 --> 02:05.331
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
THAT YOU NEVER WANTED
TO TALK TO ME AGAIN.

02:07.748 --> 02:09.576
WHAT IS IT?
ARE YOUR MOTHER
AND SISTER OKAY?

02:09.646 --> 02:11.647
OH, SO NOW YOU CARE
ABOUT OUR FAMILY?

02:11.717 --> 02:15.306
[ mumbles ]
WELL, I HAVE
A VERY BUSY DAY.

02:15.376 --> 02:18.828
I REALLY DON'T HAVE
TIME TO REHASH THINGS THAT
HAPPENED IN THE PAST, SO...

02:21.348 --> 02:23.866
LOOK, I NEED YOUR HELP
GETTING INTO THE BLOOD
DRIVE DOWNSTAIRS.

02:23.936 --> 02:25.868
I'M TRYING
TO GET AN INTERVIEW
WITH RICHIE MIRANDA.

02:25.937 --> 02:28.389
HE HASN'T SPOKEN TO THE PRESS
SINCE HE GOT OUT OF REHAB.

02:28.457 --> 02:31.703
WOW, SO YOU'VE FINALLY
BECOME A REPORTER, HUH?

02:31.771 --> 02:35.361
NOT YET. STILL ENTRY LEVEL,
BUT IF I GET THIS INTERVIEW,

02:35.430 --> 02:37.295
MY BOSS MIGHT
FINALLY LEARN MY NAME.

02:37.364 --> 02:40.918
ALL I NEED IS YOUR HELP
GETTING PAST SECURITY.
I'LL DO THE REST.

02:40.987 --> 02:43.542
Woman on intercom:
Dr. Carver, your patient
is ready in 302.

02:43.610 --> 02:46.475
WELL, I HAVE
A PATIENT WAITING, SO.

02:47.477 --> 02:50.031
RIGHT.
SHOULD'VE KNOWN.

02:50.099 --> 02:54.346
DAD ALWAYS SAID
THE ONLY PEOPLE UNCLE GEORGE
CARES ABOUT ARE HIS PATIENTS.

02:56.728 --> 02:58.349
APRIL, WAIT.

02:58.418 --> 03:00.387
...FOR COMING.
I'LL GET YOU IN A MINUTE.

03:00.455 --> 03:02.354
- Man: YOU'RE THE MAN, BABY!
- I'LL GET YOU IN A MINUTE,
I PROMISE.

03:02.423 --> 03:04.390
HOW ARE YOU DOING?
GOOD TO SEE YOU GUYS.
THANKS FOR COMING.

03:04.460 --> 03:06.426
HOW ARE YOU DOING, DUDE?
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

03:06.496 --> 03:07.739
HI, HOW ARE
YOU DOING, MY MAN? HI.

03:07.807 --> 03:09.498
HOW ARE YOU DOING?
GUESS IT'S TRUE WHAT THEY SAY,

03:09.568 --> 03:11.984
BOSTON REALLY DOES
BLEED FOR THEIR TEAM.

03:12.052 --> 03:14.538
[ laughs ]
HI.

03:14.608 --> 03:17.610
- [ laughs ]
- THANKS FOR GIVING BLOOD TODAY.

03:17.680 --> 03:20.475
I JUST HAD TO MEET
MY FAVORITE BASEBALL PLAYER.

03:20.545 --> 03:22.546
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I'M HERE.

03:22.615 --> 03:24.617
I HATE BLOOD
AND NEEDLES.

03:24.687 --> 03:27.723
- I'M SORRY.
- HEY, IF THERE WERE MORE
GIRLS WHO LOOK LIKE YOU

03:27.793 --> 03:30.243
AT BLOOD DRIVES,
I'D HAVE A NEEDLE
IN MY ARM ALL THE TIME.

03:30.312 --> 03:33.004
- [ laughs ]
- PROBABLY SHOULDN'T
JOKE ABOUT THAT.

03:33.074 --> 03:35.800
OH, WHATEVER.
I DON'T BELIEVE ANY
OF THE STUFF PEOPLE ARE SAYING.

03:35.870 --> 03:37.286
YEAH? GOOD.

03:37.354 --> 03:40.875
I MEAN YOU PROBABLY JUST
TOOK THE FALL FOR SOMEONE
ELSE ON THE TEAM.

03:40.944 --> 03:43.463
BUT IF IT WAS YOU,

03:43.533 --> 03:45.362
I WOULDN'T JUDGE.
WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES.

03:45.432 --> 03:46.847
YOU'D STILL BE MY FAVORITE.

03:48.606 --> 03:50.989
SERIOUSLY, YOU CAN TELL ME.

03:51.057 --> 03:52.921
WHAT ARE YOU, A REPORTER?

03:52.990 --> 03:54.924
NO!

03:54.992 --> 03:56.062
YOU ARE, AREN'T YOU?

03:56.132 --> 03:58.686
NO.
[ scoffs ]

03:58.754 --> 04:01.205
- WAIT, NO WAIT.
- HEY, SECURITY, HEY!

04:01.275 --> 04:03.484
- WAIT!
- I TOLD YOU NO PRESS!

04:03.552 --> 04:05.383
CAN WE GET HER
OUT OF HERE PLEASE?

04:05.451 --> 04:07.454
I REALLY DO HAVE
A THING ABOUT BLOOD.

04:27.163 --> 04:29.475
[ monitor beeping ]

04:33.273 --> 04:35.689
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
[ clears throat ]

04:35.757 --> 04:38.899
YOU FAINTED.
I WAS CHECKING
YOUR VITALS.

04:38.968 --> 04:41.832
THERE'S NO ONE ELSE
IN THIS ENTIRE HOSPITAL
WHO COULD DO THAT?

04:41.901 --> 04:44.593
RELAX, I'M DONE.

04:46.596 --> 04:49.841
HEY, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE HERE.

04:49.909 --> 04:52.499
YOU CAN'T REALLY LEAVE
A GIRL WHO BLEEDS
ALL OVER YOU

04:52.567 --> 04:54.052
IN FRONT OF A CROWD
OF PEOPLE.

04:54.120 --> 04:57.468
I'D END UP ALL OVER
THE INTERNET... AGAIN.

04:57.538 --> 05:01.093
ANYWAY, NOW THAT
I SEE YOU'RE OKAY:

05:01.161 --> 05:02.509
PEACE.

05:02.577 --> 05:04.579
I'M NOT, ACTUALLY!
I'M DYING

05:04.649 --> 05:06.547
AND THE ONLY CURE IS
AN INTERVIEW WITH YOU.

05:10.067 --> 05:12.519
YOU REPORTERS ARE CRAZY,
YOU KNOW THAT?

05:12.588 --> 05:15.487
FIRST YOU BAT
YOUR EYELASHES AT ME,

05:15.555 --> 05:18.007
THEN YOU'RE IN HERE BEING
A REAL YOU-KNOW-WHAT

05:18.076 --> 05:19.766
TO SOME POOR DOCTOR
WHO'S JUST TRYING TO HELP.

05:19.836 --> 05:21.596
THAT'S MY UNCLE.

05:21.665 --> 05:24.427
YOU TALK THAT WAY
TO EVERYONE IN YOUR FAMILY?

05:24.495 --> 05:26.497
NO, IT'S JUST HE--

05:26.567 --> 05:29.707
THAT'S THE FIRST TIME
I'VE SEEN HIM SINCE
MY DAD DIED

05:29.776 --> 05:31.985
AND HE DIDN'T EVEN BOTHER
TO COME TO THE FUNERAL.

05:32.055 --> 05:34.817
- I'M SORRY.
- WHAT, ABOUT MY DAD?

05:34.886 --> 05:38.268
IT'S OKAY. I GOT A LOT
OF MONEY OUT OF IT, SO...

05:39.199 --> 05:42.100
SORRY, I GET REALLY AWKWARD
WITH EMOTIONAL STUFF

05:42.168 --> 05:44.550
- AND MAKE INAPPROPRIATE JOKES.
- UH-HUH.

05:44.620 --> 05:46.725
I GOT THAT
FROM MY DAD ACTUALLY.

05:46.793 --> 05:48.795
HE NEVER TOOK
ANYTHING SERIOUSLY EITHER.

05:48.865 --> 05:50.625
NEITHER DID MINE.

05:50.694 --> 05:54.146
HE JUST...
PASSED AWAY LAST WEEK.

05:55.389 --> 05:57.149
NO ONE REALLY CARES
ABOUT THAT STORY

05:57.218 --> 06:00.738
WHEN THERE'S THIS OTHER
WHOLE SCANDAL GOING ON.

06:00.807 --> 06:02.983
- THAT MUST BE HARD.
- IT'S COOL.

06:03.052 --> 06:04.915
I GOT HIS MOTORCYCLE.

06:04.985 --> 06:06.538
[ laughs ]

06:11.060 --> 06:13.994
NO QUESTIONS
ABOUT DRUGS, OKAY?

06:14.062 --> 06:15.822
YEAH, OKAY.

06:16.858 --> 06:18.136
[ sighs ]

06:19.274 --> 06:21.173
FIRST QUESTION-- AHEM--

06:21.242 --> 06:23.175
WHAT WAS THE LAST THING
YOU PUT UP YOUR NOSE?

06:23.244 --> 06:24.660
[ laughs ]

06:29.146 --> 06:32.149
BILL, WHERE ARE WE
WITH THE CAMPAIGN FINANCE
REFORM PIECE?

06:32.218 --> 06:35.255
- WE GET A QUOTE FROM SIENA?
- THEIR OFFICE IS GETTING
BACK TO ME.

06:35.324 --> 06:38.605
- SO NO.
- [ coughing ]

06:42.711 --> 06:45.163
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOUR NAME,
SO I ASSUME YOU'RE ONE
OF OUR FLOATERS.

06:46.819 --> 06:48.959
THANK YOU FOR EXPOSING
THE ENTIRE SENIOR STAFF

06:49.028 --> 06:51.134
- TO YOUR GERMS.
- IT'S ALLERGIES.

06:52.757 --> 06:55.103
[ huffs ]
AND NOW

06:55.173 --> 06:57.105
MAY I TAKE A MOMENT
TO EXPRESS MY UTTER DISBELIEF

06:57.175 --> 06:59.557
THAT MARK,
MY AWARD-WINNING
SPORTSWRITER,

06:59.625 --> 07:02.213
HAS NOT GOTTEN US
RICHIE MIRANDA.

07:02.283 --> 07:04.838
I'VE BEEN
TO FENWAY EVERY MORNING.
IT'S A FORTRESS.

07:04.906 --> 07:07.218
EVEN THE BLOOD DRIVE
WAS NO PRESS,

07:07.288 --> 07:09.117
I TRIED.
MIRANDA DOESN'T
WANT TO TALK.

07:09.187 --> 07:11.706
SINCE WHEN DOES ANYBODY WANT
TO TALK TO THE PRESS?

07:11.776 --> 07:13.259
BREAK INTO
HIS GATED COMMUNITY,

07:13.329 --> 07:15.606
FIND OUT WHERE ONE
OF HIS ILLEGITIMATE KIDS
GOES TO SCHOOL.

07:15.675 --> 07:18.023
DO WHATEVER YOU HAVE TO.

07:18.091 --> 07:19.990
START ANY TIME.

07:22.925 --> 07:24.201
SORRY?

07:24.271 --> 07:26.134
YOUR LONG AND BORING
TALE OF WHY YOU'RE LATE

07:26.204 --> 07:28.309
TO A MEETING
YOU'RE NOT EVEN NECESSARY AT.

07:28.377 --> 07:30.207
- UH--
- YOU KNOW, HONESTLY

07:30.276 --> 07:33.106
I SHOULD JUST REPLACE
FLOATERS WITH COMPUTERS.

07:33.175 --> 07:36.213
COMPUTERS ARE NEVER LATE
AND THEY DON'T GET SICK.

07:36.283 --> 07:38.319
- [ coughs ]
- YEAH, UM,

07:38.387 --> 07:40.701
I'M PLANNING ON
USING ONE TO TYPE UP
MY INTERVIEW

07:40.769 --> 07:42.254
WITH RICHIE MIRANDA.

07:44.255 --> 07:45.843
UH, WE HAD A NICE TALK.

07:45.913 --> 07:48.052
SORRY I'M LATE.
THE BLOOD DRIVE RAN LONG.

07:48.122 --> 07:51.262
THE BLOOD DRIVE WHERE
NO PRESS WAS ALLOWED?

07:51.331 --> 07:53.093
WE'LL RUN IT
IN SUNDAY SPORTS.

07:53.161 --> 07:55.060
- I'LL GET YOU
A DRAFT BY TOMORROW.
- OH NO, YOU WON'T.

07:55.129 --> 07:58.132
FLOATERS DON'T WRITE
FEATURE STORIES IN
MAJOR NEWSPAPERS.

07:58.201 --> 08:01.204
MEET WITH MARK
FIRST THING TOMORROW MORNING,
DOWNLOAD YOUR NOTES TO HIM.

08:02.826 --> 08:05.105
NORA, CAN YOU WRITE A PIECE
ABOUT THE ECONOMY

08:05.173 --> 08:07.901
THAT WON'T MAKE ME
WANT TO KILL MYSELF?

08:07.970 --> 08:09.696
- [ phones ringing ]
- [ keyboard clacking ]

08:15.184 --> 08:16.737
WHAT, DID YOU
SLEEP WITH HIM?

08:16.805 --> 08:19.119
IT'S SO UNFAIR YOU GET
TO HAVE SEX FOR A STORY
AND I DON'T.

08:19.187 --> 08:21.223
DANNY, YOU KNOW
HOW PICKY I AM.

08:21.293 --> 08:23.192
I'M NOT GONNA SLEEP
WITH SOME DIRTY
SPORTS STAR

08:23.261 --> 08:25.262
WHO PROBABLY, LIKE,
CHEWS TOBACCO.

08:25.331 --> 08:28.059
AND I DON'T EVEN GET
TO WRITE THE STORY
AFTER ALL THAT.

08:28.127 --> 08:31.026
GUESS IT'S CALLED
"PAYING YOUR DUES."

08:31.096 --> 08:33.270
I DID NOT SPEND FOUR YEARS
AT HARVARD TO PAY MY DUES.

08:35.962 --> 08:38.068
[ male singer vocalizing ]

08:41.520 --> 08:44.177
- HEY, APRIL,
CAN I BORROW A TISSUE?
- FINALLY ADMITTING YOU'RE SICK?

08:44.246 --> 08:46.663
NO, YOU'RE JUST
DROOLING A LITTLE.

08:46.732 --> 08:49.389
JUST ASK HIM OUT.
AREN'T YOU ONE OF THOSE
ANNOYING GIRLS

08:49.459 --> 08:51.115
- THAT DOES THAT?
- A FEMINIST?

08:51.184 --> 08:53.325
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I SAID--
ONE OF THOSE ANNOYING GIRLS.

08:53.394 --> 08:55.913
I DON'T KNOW,
IT'S DIFFERENT. DOMINIC'S,
LIKE, AN ACTUAL REPORTER HERE.

08:55.982 --> 08:58.330
ARTS AND ENTERTAINMENT?
PLEASE.

08:58.399 --> 09:01.298
YOU'RE SUCH A SNOB.
AND I CAN'T JUST START
SEXUALLY HARASSING HIM.

09:01.368 --> 09:02.851
WE JUST HAD THAT SEMINAR.

09:02.921 --> 09:05.785
I THINK IT'S JUST SEXUAL
HARASSMENT WHEN THE POWER
GOES THE OTHER WAY.

09:05.855 --> 09:07.649
IN THIS CASE
YOU'RE UNDER DOMINIC...

09:07.719 --> 09:09.618
OR WISH YOU WERE.

09:09.687 --> 09:11.342
[ elevator dings ]

09:16.900 --> 09:18.211
OH HEY, CAN YOU HOLD THAT?

09:24.390 --> 09:26.807
YOU REALLY
WANTED THIS ELEVATOR
TO YOURSELF, HUH?

09:26.875 --> 09:28.774
YEAH, DO YOU MIND
TAKING THE STAIRS?

09:28.844 --> 09:32.087
SO I HEARD EVERYONE
ON THE SENIOR STAFF
HATES YOU NOW.

09:32.157 --> 09:33.951
- WHAT?
- ACTUALLY
I DIDN'T HEAR THAT.

09:34.020 --> 09:36.298
BUT I'D HATE YOU.
YOU'VE BEEN HERE,
WHAT, SIX MONTHS

09:36.368 --> 09:38.508
- AND YOU ALREADY
GOT A BIG INTERVIEW?
- YEAH.

09:38.577 --> 09:41.960
MY LIFE IS REALLY GLAMOROUS.
NOW I GET TO GO HOME AND HAVE
DINNER WITH MY MOM

09:42.028 --> 09:44.238
AND MY GRANDMA,
WHO I LIVE WITH

09:44.307 --> 09:46.240
BECAUSE I CAN'T
AFFORD MY OWN PLACE.

09:46.308 --> 09:48.241
WELL, IF YOU FEEL LIKE
GETTING AWAY LATER,

09:48.311 --> 09:50.831
I'M COVERING A SHOW
AT THE HANGOVER AT 9:00.

09:50.899 --> 09:52.902
I COULD USE
A SECOND OPINION
IF YOU'RE FREE.

09:52.971 --> 09:55.697
YEAH, THAT SHOULD WORK.

09:55.767 --> 09:57.182
[ elevator dings ]

09:57.250 --> 09:59.390
♪ I WANT IT, I NEED IT ♪

09:59.460 --> 10:01.773
♪ I WANT SOMEBODY ♪

10:01.841 --> 10:03.706
♪ I WANT IT, I NEED IT ♪

10:03.774 --> 10:07.123
♪ I WANT YOUR LIES
TO TURN, I NEED IT ♪

10:07.192 --> 10:11.541
♪ I want it,
I want somebody, baby ♪

10:11.610 --> 10:14.371
♪ Now this is my turn ♪

10:14.441 --> 10:17.547
♪ I don't want
any more doors ♪

10:18.548 --> 10:20.929
- ♪ 'Cause I want to... ♪
- EXCUSE ME, MISS.

10:20.999 --> 10:23.000
THIS AREA IS
FOR EMPLOYEES ONLY.

10:23.070 --> 10:25.347
WELL, IF SOMEONE WERE
ACTUALLY RUNNING THE STORE,

10:25.417 --> 10:28.489
MAYBE I WOULDN'T HAVE
TO MAKE MY OWN COFFEE.
I MISS THE OLD MANAGER.

10:28.557 --> 10:30.559
I DON'T.
SHE WAS A LAZY BITCH.

10:30.629 --> 10:32.942
MM, NO, SHE WASN'T.
SHE WAS A GENIUS.

10:33.010 --> 10:35.357
- AND SUPER HOT.
CAN I GET HER NUMBER?
- [ giggles ]

10:35.427 --> 10:38.360
SO TELL ME EVERYTHING.
DOMINIC ASKED YOU OUT?

10:38.429 --> 10:40.328
UH, I MEAN
NOT TECHNICALLY.

10:40.398 --> 10:43.125
- IT'S WORK-RELATED.
- SO MAKE IT NOT WORK-RELATED.

10:43.193 --> 10:45.298
FEED HIM TEQUILA SHOTS
AND PIN HIM AGAINST
A WALL-- DONE.

10:45.368 --> 10:47.094
- MM, NO.
- OKAY,

10:47.163 --> 10:49.164
OR YOU COULD BE
A PRUDE AND TALK
ABOUT YOUR FEELINGS.

10:49.234 --> 10:51.167
I'M SURE THIS DUDE
WOULD BE INTO THAT.

10:51.235 --> 10:53.066
HE HAS A SCENTED CANDLE
ON HIS DESK.

10:53.134 --> 10:55.067
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE
TOLD YOU ABOUT THAT CANDLE.

10:55.136 --> 10:58.243
IT SMELLS LIKE TREES.
IT'S NOT, LIKE, VANILLA.

10:58.312 --> 11:01.177
WHATEVER.
IT'S STILL A LITTLE
METROSEXUAL FOR ME.

11:01.245 --> 11:03.178
I PREFER STRONG,
SILENT TYPES

11:03.248 --> 11:06.975
WHO WATCH SPORTS AND--
AND SHOOT GUNS.

11:07.044 --> 11:09.357
BETH, THAT MAKES NO SENSE.

11:09.427 --> 11:12.947
YOU WATCH
"DOWNTON ABBEY" AND DONATE
TO THE AUDUBON SOCIETY.

11:13.017 --> 11:14.466
- [ cellphone chimes ]
- SINCE WHEN DOES
THE BRAIN GOVERN

11:14.534 --> 11:16.813
WHO WE WANT
TO SEE NAKED?

11:16.883 --> 11:20.024
UGH, UNCLE GEORGE.

11:20.092 --> 11:21.818
HAVEN'T HEARD
THAT NAME IN A WHILE.

11:21.888 --> 11:24.303
I KNOW. I SAW HIM
AT THAT BLOOD DRIVE
THIS MORNING

11:24.373 --> 11:27.409
AND NOW I THINK HE WANTS
TO, LIKE, BE BACK IN TOUCH.

11:27.479 --> 11:29.171
AND I-- I JUST--
I CAN'T.

11:30.379 --> 11:33.209
- UGH. OH, HE'S SO AWKWARD.
- RIGHT?

11:33.278 --> 11:35.279
HE EVEN SIGNED
THE TEXT "FROM GEORGE."

11:35.349 --> 11:39.008
YOU KNOW WHAT?
JUST IGNORE HIM.
HE'LL GET THE MESSAGE.

11:39.076 --> 11:41.528
OR MAYBE
HE JUST FEELS AWKWARD
TELLING YOU THEY CAN'T

11:41.596 --> 11:44.254
USE YOUR BLOOD FROM THE DRIVE
BECAUSE YOU HAVE AN S.T.D.

11:44.323 --> 11:46.326
- GOD, COULD YOU IMAGINE?
- COMING FROM YOUR UNCLE?

11:46.394 --> 11:48.259
"YOU HAVE HERPES.
FROM GEORGE."

11:52.297 --> 11:54.334
- [ video game beeping ]
- OH!

11:54.403 --> 11:57.336
- MOM, YOU OKAY?
- SHE'S PLAYING BRIDGE ROULETTE.

11:57.405 --> 12:00.374
I WOULDN'T CALL IT PLAYING.
THESE DUMMIES DON'T
EVEN KNOW HOW.

12:00.442 --> 12:02.480
IT'S ROULETTE.
JUST SWITCH TO
THE NEXT PLAYER.

12:02.548 --> 12:05.827
IF I QUIT,
MY RATING GOES DOWN
AND I WILL NOT BE RANKED LOWER

12:05.897 --> 12:09.176
THAN SOME FOOL IN INDIANAPOLIS
WITH A "HELLO KITTY" AVATAR.

12:09.245 --> 12:11.453
BRENNA, WILL YOU
SET THE TABLE?

12:11.523 --> 12:14.354
CAN'T. I'M WORKING
ON MY COMMUNITY
OUTREACH STUFF.

12:14.423 --> 12:16.217
OH!

12:17.495 --> 12:19.289
ALL RIGHT, NEVER MIND.

12:20.567 --> 12:22.431
MOM, WHAT IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

12:22.500 --> 12:25.296
I'M JUST PROUD OF YOU!
AND I WANT TO REMIND YOU

12:25.365 --> 12:28.230
WHERE YOU WERE LAST YEAR.
COMPARED TO NOW, IT'S--

12:28.298 --> 12:30.438
WHAT AN ACCOMPLISHMENT
WHEN A CHILD--

12:30.508 --> 12:33.960
- OH MY GOD.
- HEY, I TELL MY PATIENTS
ALL THE TIME,

12:34.028 --> 12:36.825
PRAISE YOUR KIDS
WHEN THEY EXCEL.

12:36.894 --> 12:40.206
I KNOW HOW TOUGH IT'S BEEN
THESE COUPLE OF YEARS FOR YOU.

12:40.275 --> 12:42.278
NOT JUST YOU,
THIS WHOLE FAMILY.

12:42.346 --> 12:46.005
BUT, BRENNA, WHEN YOU WERE
CUTTING CLASSES AND BLOWING
OFF YOUR SCHOOLWORK

12:46.075 --> 12:49.284
- FOR THAT BOYFRIEND OF
YOURS--
- OKAY, SEAN WAS NEVER
MY BOYFRIEND.

12:49.354 --> 12:52.149
OKAY, REGARDLESS.
IT'S JUST ON TOP OF
EVERYTHING ELSE,

12:52.219 --> 12:54.289
GETTING THE PHONE CALLS
EVERY DAY FROM SCHOOL--

12:54.359 --> 12:56.360
OKAY, I'M NOT BLAMING--
THIS IS NOT--

12:56.429 --> 12:58.432
"DEAR MOM:
PLEASE FINISH A SENTENCE.
THANKS, BRENNA."

12:58.500 --> 13:01.090
"DEAR BRENNA: PLEASE STOP
COMMUNICATING WITH PEOPLE

13:01.158 --> 13:03.264
BY WRITING
LETTERS FROM YOURSELF.
THANKS, APRIL."

13:05.404 --> 13:07.234
SO...

13:07.302 --> 13:09.547
I HAVE A LITTLE
ANNOUNCEMENT.

13:10.616 --> 13:13.895
I'M THINKING OF JOINING
ONE OF THOSE ONLINE
DATING SERVICES

13:13.965 --> 13:16.623
- YOU GUYS KEEP TALKING ABOUT.
- YOU'RE TOO YOUNG TO DATE.

13:16.692 --> 13:18.279
WAIT, MOM,
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

13:18.349 --> 13:20.419
I'M THINKING ABOUT IT.
I DON'T KNOW.

13:20.489 --> 13:23.181
I MEAN I'M A THERAPIST,
WOULDN'T IT LOOK TOO
UNPROFESSIONAL--

13:23.250 --> 13:25.976
NO! WHATEVER. I'M TAKING
YOUR PROFILE PICTURE.

13:26.046 --> 13:27.427
WAIT, NO,
I WANNA DO IT.

13:27.495 --> 13:29.255
- HOLD ON, WAIT WAIT WAIT.
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE BUSY.

13:29.325 --> 13:31.326
- I WANT TO DO IT.
- CAN YOU BELIEVE
I'M DOING THIS?

13:31.395 --> 13:34.123
DON'T LOOK AT ME.
I THINK YOU'RE ASKING
TO END UP IN A BODY BAG.

13:34.192 --> 13:36.504
- SHH.
- [ exhales ]

13:36.573 --> 13:40.232
- MOM, SMILE LIKE
A NORMAL PERSON.
- WELL, I AM!

13:40.302 --> 13:42.442
- AHEM.
- [ camera clicks ]

13:42.510 --> 13:44.615
LET'S TRY SERIOUS THEN.

13:44.684 --> 13:46.273
- [ clicks ]
- [ snickering ]

13:46.341 --> 13:47.965
OKAY, MOM, EW.

13:48.033 --> 13:50.000
- [ all laugh ]
- WHAT-- DON'T--

13:50.070 --> 13:51.623
ALL RIGHT, DELETE DELETE!

13:53.279 --> 13:56.765
[ strumming ukulele ]

13:56.836 --> 14:00.322
♪ FICKLE FICKLE,
LITTLE HEART ♪

14:00.390 --> 14:02.530
- ♪ HOW IT HURTS
WHEN WE'RE APART... ♪
- I AM SO SORRY.

14:02.600 --> 14:05.222
I CANNOT WAIT
TO READ YOUR REVIEW.

14:05.292 --> 14:07.363
I FEEL BAD FOR HER
WHEN SHE READS IT.

14:07.432 --> 14:09.640
MM, I DON'T KNOW,
IS SHE OLD ENOUGH TO READ?

14:09.710 --> 14:11.953
I THINK
I HAD THAT DRESS
IN KINDERGARTEN.

14:12.023 --> 14:14.508
AND I HAD THAT VOICE.

14:14.576 --> 14:16.337
ANOTHER BEER?

14:17.546 --> 14:19.065
YEAH, I CAN GET IT.

14:19.134 --> 14:22.206
[ sighs ]
I KNOW BUT I'M OFFERING.

14:22.274 --> 14:24.484
TWO MORE PLEASE.
IT'S DOLLAR-BEER NIGHT.

14:24.552 --> 14:26.037
I THINK I CAN HANDLE IT.

14:27.418 --> 14:29.316
YOU ARE NOT
MAKING THIS EASY.

14:29.384 --> 14:31.110
MAKING WHAT EASY?

14:31.179 --> 14:32.216
YOU GET YOUR OWN BEERS,

14:32.284 --> 14:33.630
YOU GOT YOUR OWN
COVER CHARGE,

14:33.700 --> 14:35.322
YOU HELD THE DOOR FOR ME.

14:38.187 --> 14:40.188
I HAVE A CONFESSION.

14:40.258 --> 14:42.259
I'M NOT REVIEWING
THIS SHOW.

14:43.365 --> 14:44.606
- YOU'RE NOT?
- NO.

14:44.676 --> 14:47.506
I JUST WANTED TO SEE YOU
OUTSIDE THE OFFICE.

14:47.576 --> 14:50.543
- OH.
- BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
WE KINDA JOKE AROUND AT WORK,

14:50.613 --> 14:53.236
AND I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'RE JUST BEING FUNNY

14:53.306 --> 14:55.998
OR IF... WE'RE FLIRTING.

14:56.067 --> 14:58.345
WELL, ARE YOU FLIRTING?

14:58.413 --> 15:01.003
I FEEL LIKE IF I ANSWER
THIS HONESTLY--

15:01.072 --> 15:03.246
I'M JUST THINKING ABOUT
THAT SEXUAL-HARASSMENT SEMINAR.

15:03.316 --> 15:05.179
- I WAS JUST TALKING ABOUT THAT!
- OH, YOU WERE?

15:05.249 --> 15:08.562
IN WHAT CONTEXT?
WERE YOU TALKING ABOUT DATING
ONE OF YOUR COWORKERS?

15:08.630 --> 15:11.600
I CAN'T REALLY REMEMBER.
I THINK IT WAS JUST IN CASE

15:11.668 --> 15:14.222
SOMEONE STARTED
WORKING THERE THAT I LIKED.

15:16.225 --> 15:18.606
[ April in nasally voice ]
"WE NEED TO CALL SERVICE
FOR THE COPIER.

15:18.676 --> 15:21.333
- DID SOMEBODY CALL SERVICE?"
- PAM FROM HUMAN RESOURCES!

15:21.403 --> 15:23.094
UH...

15:23.163 --> 15:25.441
[ nerdy voice ]
"THERE'S LEFTOVER PIZZA
IN THE BREAK ROOM.

15:25.509 --> 15:27.719
- IT'S SAUSAGE."
- OH DUH, GEOFFREY
FROM CLASSIFIEDS.

15:27.788 --> 15:30.619
OKAY, THIS NEXT ONE
REQUIRES A CONVERSATION.

15:30.687 --> 15:33.241
SO START TELLING ME
ABOUT YOUR DAY SO FAR.

15:33.311 --> 15:36.383
OKAY, I WOKE UP
TO MY LITTLE SISTER'S
ALARM CLOCK RINGING--

15:36.451 --> 15:38.177
"I KNOW HER.
I DATED HER."

15:38.246 --> 15:40.215
AND THEN I THINK
I TURNED ON C.N.N.--

15:40.283 --> 15:42.734
"I WATCH THAT, AND B.B.C.
THAT'S THE ONLY TV I WATCH.

15:42.802 --> 15:45.875
- I USUALLY JUST
LISTEN TO N.P.R."
- OH, DANNY GUPTA.

15:45.945 --> 15:47.669
SORRY, I KNOW
HE'S YOUR FRIEND.

15:47.739 --> 15:50.052
OH IT'S FINE.
I TELL HIM THIS STUFF
TO HIS FACE.

15:50.120 --> 15:52.226
I BET YOU DO.
YOU DON'T SEEM LIKE THE TYPE
TO BEAT AROUND THE BUSH.

15:52.296 --> 15:54.918
OOH, ALSO NOT THE TYPE
TO USE THE EXPRESSION
"BEAT AROUND THE BUSH."

15:54.988 --> 15:58.404
- [ phone rings ]
- OH, WHO'S GEORGE?

15:58.474 --> 16:01.201
- BOOTY CALL?
- NO. GROSS.

16:01.269 --> 16:03.479
SEE, YOU REALLY DIDN'T
BEAT AROUND THE BUSH THERE.

16:03.548 --> 16:05.378
OH MY GOD.
EVERY TIME YOU SAY IT

16:05.447 --> 16:08.173
MY ENTIRE BODY CRINGES
WITH EMBARRASSMENT FOR YOU.

16:08.243 --> 16:10.554
- BEAT AROUND THE BUSH.
- OH, I HATE YOU.

16:10.624 --> 16:13.282
OH, I GOT--
I GOT ONE MORE
IMPRESSION FOR YOU.

16:14.558 --> 16:15.595
ARE YOU READY?

16:20.461 --> 16:22.671
♪ LITTLE LIGHT SHINING
IN THE DARK ♪

16:24.327 --> 16:26.674
♪ AND THEY SHOW US
THE WAY ♪

16:26.744 --> 16:29.366
♪ ONE LIGHTS UP
EVERY TIME YOU FEEL LOVE... ♪

16:29.436 --> 16:31.162
MAUREEN
FROM ACCOUNTING?

16:32.508 --> 16:34.648
♪ ONE DIES
WHEN IT MOVES AWAY. ♪

16:38.375 --> 16:40.344
[ phone ringing ]

16:50.905 --> 16:53.770
[ whispering ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
DO YOU KNOW HOW LATE IT IS?

16:53.840 --> 16:56.394
YES, I KNOW, I KNOW.
BUT IT'S-- IT'S IMPORTANT.

16:56.462 --> 16:59.293
LOOK, I APPRECIATE
YOUR HELP TODAY, REALLY.

16:59.363 --> 17:01.433
BUT WHAT IF MY MOM
WAKES UP?

17:01.503 --> 17:03.331
SHE WOULD KILL ME
IF SHE EVEN KNEW I SAW YOU.

17:03.400 --> 17:06.300
- ALL RIGHT, APRIL--
- AND YOU KNOW, YOU NEVER
BOTHERED TO COME AROUND

17:06.369 --> 17:08.509
WHEN WE TRIED TO MAKE YOU
PART OF THE FAMILY BEFORE,

17:08.578 --> 17:10.511
SO IT'S NOT LIKE YOU CAN
JUST SHOW UP NOW--

17:10.580 --> 17:13.134
ALL RIGHT, APRIL,
IT'S NOT ABOUT ME.
IT'S ABOUT YOUR HEALTH.

17:13.203 --> 17:15.378
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

17:15.448 --> 17:17.897
AFTER YOU FAINTED TODAY,

17:17.967 --> 17:20.348
I RAN SOME TESTS
ON YOUR BLOOD.

17:23.490 --> 17:25.250
WHAT?

17:28.219 --> 17:30.325
YOU HAVE CANCER.

17:34.846 --> 17:36.572
[ scoffs ]

17:40.299 --> 17:43.476
- I'M 24.
- I KNOW.

17:48.480 --> 17:52.036
- WHAT KIND OF...?
- IT'S LEUKEMIA.

17:52.105 --> 17:54.728
BUT WE HAVE TO RUN
SOME MORE TESTS

17:54.797 --> 17:58.455
TO DETERMINE EXACTLY
WHAT THE SUBTYPE IS.

17:58.525 --> 18:00.803
UM...

18:00.872 --> 18:03.910
WE CAN-- WE CAN-- WE CAN
TREAT IT THOUGH, RIGHT?

18:03.979 --> 18:05.876
- IT'S TREATABLE?
- YEAH.

18:05.945 --> 18:09.467
- OKAY, GOOD.
- TREATING ISN'T
THE SAME AS CURING.

18:09.536 --> 18:11.675
WHATEVER, HOW DO WE--
HOW DO WE CURE IT THEN?

18:13.471 --> 18:15.472
I'M GONNA BE OKAY, RIGHT?

18:15.541 --> 18:19.374
AS I SAY, WE HAVE
TO RUN MORE TESTS.

18:19.442 --> 18:22.203
- [ window slides ]
- APRIL, IS THAT YOU?

18:22.272 --> 18:24.275
YEAH!
SORRY, GRANDMA,

18:24.344 --> 18:26.519
I WAS JUST MAKING
A PHONE CALL FOR WORK.

18:26.587 --> 18:28.865
NOW? THEY'D BETTER
BE PAYING YOU OVERTIME!

18:28.934 --> 18:30.661
[ sighs ]
I WISH.

18:30.730 --> 18:32.627
UM, I'LL BE UP
IN A MINUTE.

18:32.697 --> 18:34.560
OKAY.

18:39.531 --> 18:42.017
- UH, I HAVE TO GO.
- SO-- OKAY.

18:42.086 --> 18:45.744
BUT YOU-- COME TO MY OFFICE
TOMORROW, WE'LL TALK ABOUT
EVERYTHING THERE.

18:45.814 --> 18:49.266
- I'LL FIND ANOTHER DOCTOR.
- WHY? I'M AN ONCOLOGIST.

18:49.335 --> 18:52.614
- I'M ONE OF
THE BEST IN THE STATE.
- AT A CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL.

18:52.682 --> 18:54.511
[ sighs ]

18:54.580 --> 18:58.344
PLEASE, JUST COME BY,
DO THE TESTS.

18:58.413 --> 19:01.242
YOU KNOW IT'S
IN YOUR BEST INTEREST
TO LET ME HELP YOU,

19:01.311 --> 19:04.590
DESPITE WHATEVER
YOU MAY THINK ABOUT ME
ON A PERSONAL LEVEL.

19:06.317 --> 19:08.354
- FINE.
- OKAY.

19:08.423 --> 19:11.909
SO I'LL SEE YOU THERE
TOMORROW FIRST THING,
LIKE 8:00, 8:30?

19:11.978 --> 19:15.291
- I HAVE A STAFF MEETING THEN.
- YOU DO KNOW HOW SERIOUS
THIS IS, RIGHT?

19:15.361 --> 19:17.983
YES, I JUST DON'T
WANT TO LOSE MY JOB

19:18.053 --> 19:20.434
IN ADDITION TO... THIS.

19:21.435 --> 19:23.265
CAN I COME IN
AT LUNCH, PLEASE?

19:23.334 --> 19:26.474
YEAH SURE, OKAY, YEAH, OKAY.
I'LL SEE-- SEE YOU TOMORROW.

19:27.890 --> 19:29.478
I'M SORRY.

19:29.547 --> 19:31.653
[ keys jingling ]

19:32.171 --> 19:34.621
[ lock clicks, door opens ]

19:44.873 --> 19:46.770
MOM.

19:48.427 --> 19:50.534
I GOTTA JUST GO GET

19:50.603 --> 19:53.709
SOME GREEN PEPPERS
FROM WILSON FARM

19:53.778 --> 19:55.503
FOR THE SALAD.

20:09.208 --> 20:11.933
♪ SOMETIMES YOU FEEL ♪

20:12.002 --> 20:14.522
- ♪ LIKE YOU AREN'T... ♪
- MOM.

20:16.041 --> 20:18.388
- ♪ WHO YOU ARE... ♪
- SOMETHING'S WRONG WITH ME.

20:21.150 --> 20:23.429
[ crickets chirping ]

20:24.636 --> 20:26.846
♪ SURE, WE WILL LOVE ♪

20:26.914 --> 20:29.469
♪ AND WE WILL LISTEN... ♪

20:39.548 --> 20:42.895
♪ CAUGHT ♪

20:42.964 --> 20:45.898
♪ BETWEEN THE CRACK'S
BRIGHT LIGHTS ♪

20:45.968 --> 20:49.039
- ♪ INVISIBLE. ♪
- MORNING.

20:49.108 --> 20:51.387
- MORNING.
- IS MOM AROUND?

20:51.457 --> 20:53.078
NO, SHE HAD
AN EARLY PATIENT.

20:53.147 --> 20:56.082
SHE WOKE ME UP.
SHE ALWAYS MAKES SO MUCH
NOISE IN THE KITCHEN.

20:56.151 --> 20:58.877
DECIDED I'D JUST TAKE
THESE OLD BONES FOR A SPIN.

20:58.947 --> 21:01.190
YOU'RE IN BETTER SHAPE
THAN I AM.

21:01.259 --> 21:02.984
I LOVE IT
WHEN YOU LIE TO ME.

21:07.126 --> 21:09.544
- [ door closes ]
- Brenna: IT'S "COMMUNITY
OUTREACH" DAY.

21:09.613 --> 21:12.339
IT'LL BE EASY.
HE'S PICKING US UP AFTER SCHOOL.

21:12.409 --> 21:14.030
YEAH.

21:14.099 --> 21:15.998
WE SHOULD DO THAT, TOO.

21:16.067 --> 21:18.104
YEAH, I KNOW.

21:18.173 --> 21:22.038
- WHAT'S UP, STALKER?
- WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

21:22.107 --> 21:24.835
- CHELSEA, WHY?
- ARE YOU SKIPPING
COMMUNITY OUTREACH?

21:24.903 --> 21:27.976
- I DIDN'T SAY THAT.
- THEN WHO'S PICKING YOU UP?

21:28.045 --> 21:31.048
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- BRENNA, IF YOU'RE STILL
SEEING SEAN,

21:31.116 --> 21:33.015
I'M TELLING YOU
IT'S A WASTE OF TIME.

21:33.084 --> 21:35.914
YOU'VE BEEN CHASING HIM
FOR HOW LONG NOW AND HE'S
STILL NOT GOING FOR IT?

21:35.983 --> 21:38.503
IT'S NOT WORTH SCREWING
THIS FAMILY UP AGAIN!

21:38.573 --> 21:41.817
I'M JUST TAKING
THE "T" HOME WITH CHELSEA.
GOD, WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

21:41.885 --> 21:44.199
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW MUCH I HAD TO
TAKE CARE OF MOM

21:44.268 --> 21:47.064
WHEN YOU WERE
SNEAKING OUT AT NIGHT
AND FAILING OUT OF SCHOOL?

21:47.133 --> 21:51.550
A SCHOOL SHE'S, LIKE,
PAYING ALL OF HER MONEY
TO SEND YOU TO?

21:54.796 --> 21:57.038
SOMEONE'S
ON THEIR PERIOD!

22:00.490 --> 22:03.424
♪ THESE DAYS I JUST CAN'T
THINK STRAIGHT ♪

22:03.493 --> 22:07.117
♪ I GOT TOO MANY ANGLES
RUNNING 'ROUND MY BRAIN ♪

22:07.186 --> 22:09.086
♪ 'CAUSE I GOTTA GO,
BUT I... ♪

22:09.154 --> 22:11.468
YEAH, IF YOU COULD PROOFREAD
THAT BEFORE LUNCH,

22:11.537 --> 22:12.986
- IT'D BE AWESOME.
- YOU GOT IT.

22:15.540 --> 22:17.439
OKAY, WHO AM I?

22:17.508 --> 22:20.028
"IS IT JUST ME,
OR IS THERE SOMETHING
ABOUT WALKING DOWN THE HALL

22:20.096 --> 22:23.513
- THAT'S SO SENSUAL?"
- UM, SORRY?

22:24.549 --> 22:26.827
IT'S MALLORY
FROM "ASK MALLORY!"

22:26.896 --> 22:28.898
COME ON,
THAT WAS AN EASY ONE.

22:30.038 --> 22:31.521
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

22:31.590 --> 22:34.836
YEAH, I'M FINE.
I'M JUST A LITTLE OUT OF IT
THIS MORNING.

22:34.904 --> 22:37.320
- IT WAS A ROUGH NIGHT, HUH?
- YEAH.

22:37.390 --> 22:40.875
I MEAN NO.
UH, CAN WE CATCH UP LATER?

22:40.944 --> 22:43.016
I HAVE A MILLION THINGS
TO DO TODAY.

22:43.085 --> 22:44.810
YEAH.

22:49.090 --> 22:51.266
HEY, TASHA.
I'M MEETING WITH MARK
THIS MORNING.

22:51.335 --> 22:53.682
- IS HE IN YET?
- [ yelling ] I DIDN'T ASK
HOW YOU WERE FEELING.

22:53.750 --> 22:55.925
I ASKED TO HAVE
THE MIRANDA INTERVIEW
ON MY DESK

22:55.994 --> 22:58.203
- WHEN I GET BACK FROM LUNCH!
- MARK'S OUT WITH THE FLU.

22:58.272 --> 23:00.586
HE THINKS
ONE OF THE FLOATERS
GAVE IT TO HIM.

23:00.654 --> 23:02.726
YOU'RE NOT SICK, ARE YOU?

23:03.692 --> 23:06.246
- NO.
- I'M NOT GETTING BACK
FROM LUNCH TOMORROW!

23:06.315 --> 23:07.799
I'M GETTING BACK TODAY!

23:09.317 --> 23:10.872
ARE YOU THROWING UP
RIGHT NOW?

23:13.978 --> 23:15.980
[ typing ]

23:17.188 --> 23:18.913
THAI FOOD?
CHEESESTEAKS? PANINIS?

23:18.982 --> 23:21.571
GOD, YOU'RE LIKE
AN INDIAN JACK-IN-THE-BOX.

23:21.641 --> 23:23.711
YOU'RE WELCOME, BY THE WAY.

23:23.780 --> 23:25.852
- HMM?
- FOR GETTING MARK SICK,

23:25.921 --> 23:28.130
SO YOU COULD STEAL
HIS ASSIGNMENT?

23:29.200 --> 23:30.856
HUH? SORRY.

23:30.925 --> 23:32.789
I'M JUST-- I'M TRYING
TO TURN THIS IN
BY HIS DEADLINE.

23:32.858 --> 23:35.344
- [ alarm beeps ]
- [ sighs ]

23:35.413 --> 23:37.587
WAS THAT MARK'S DEADLINE?
BUMMER.

23:37.656 --> 23:40.211
NO, I'M SUPPOSED
TO SEE MY UNCLE.

23:40.279 --> 23:44.008
WHO CARES ABOUT YOUR UNCLE?
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW YOU HAD
AN UNCLE UNTIL JUST NOW.

23:44.076 --> 23:46.907
I'M JUST SAYING,
IF MY NANI CAME BACK
FROM THE DEAD

23:46.977 --> 23:48.943
RIGHT WHEN I NEEDED
TO FINISH A STORY?

23:49.012 --> 23:51.118
ARE YOU SAYING
YOU'D BLOW OFF YOUR DEAD
GRANDMOTHER FOR A STORY?

23:51.188 --> 23:53.741
HELL YEAH.
BUT MAYBE THAT'S JUST ME.

23:53.810 --> 23:56.848
MY CAREER IS,
LIKE, MY LIFE.

24:06.202 --> 24:08.239
ME TOO.

24:12.140 --> 24:15.074
[ printer whirrs ]

24:15.625 --> 24:17.835
YEAH. WHAT?

24:17.903 --> 24:20.286
NO ONE CALLED FOR ME
DURING LUNCH?

24:21.320 --> 24:23.910
I DON'T KNOW WHETHER
TO FEEL RELIEVED
OR REJECTED.

24:24.807 --> 24:26.913
[ cat meowing ]

24:27.982 --> 24:29.951
KEEP UP
THE GREAT WORK, BILL.

24:30.019 --> 24:32.366
NO NO, KEEP GOING.
I'M DYING TO SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

24:32.435 --> 24:34.644
- DOES HE GET THE BALL?
- SORRY.

24:35.990 --> 24:38.200
- YES, GIRL-FROM-YESTERDAY?
- UH, SORRY.

24:38.269 --> 24:41.099
- I WASN'T
LISTENING OR ANYTHING--
- WHY WEREN'T YOU LISTENING?

24:41.169 --> 24:43.585
A GOOD JOURNALIST
ALWAYS LISTENS.

24:43.653 --> 24:46.692
I KNOW YOU SAID
YOU DON'T LET FLOATERS
WRITE STORIES,

24:46.760 --> 24:48.210
BUT SINCE MARK
IS OUT, I DID A DRAFT

24:48.278 --> 24:50.211
OF THE RICHIE PIECE
JUST IN CASE IT HELPS.

24:50.280 --> 24:53.076
- NO PRESSURE,
BUT IF YOU COULD--
- George: APRIL!

24:53.145 --> 24:54.733
THERE YOU ARE.

24:54.802 --> 24:57.080
UM, I'M JUST RUNNING
INTO A MEETING.

24:59.117 --> 25:00.877
- [ April sighs ]
- I WANTED TO SEE
IF YOU WERE--

25:00.946 --> 25:02.708
STOP IT!
COME WITH ME.

25:09.127 --> 25:11.717
LOOK, I KNOW I WAS SUPPOSED
TO COME IN AT LUNCH,

25:11.786 --> 25:13.925
BUT YOU CAN'T JUST
STALK ME LIKE THIS.

25:13.994 --> 25:16.238
I JUST HAD TO MAKE SURE
THAT YOU WERE OKAY.

25:16.307 --> 25:18.136
GEORGE, I'M FINE.

25:18.205 --> 25:20.864
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M GONNA
DROP DEAD ANY SECOND.

25:22.830 --> 25:24.902
I'M NOT, RIGHT?

25:24.971 --> 25:28.009
I READ ONLINE THAT
AS LONG AS YOU DIAGNOSE
LEUKEMIA EARLY YOU CAN...

25:28.077 --> 25:31.770
BEGIN TREATMENT,
BUT WE DON'T EVEN SPECIFICALLY
KNOW WHAT WE'RE TREATING YET,

25:31.839 --> 25:34.084
WHICH IS WHY WE'VE GOT
TO ACT RIGHT AWAY,

25:34.153 --> 25:37.051
ESPECIALLY IF YOU'RE
SHOWING ANY SYMPTOMS.

25:37.121 --> 25:40.779
HAVE YOU NOTICED YOU'RE FEELING
UNUSUALLY TIRED LATELY?

25:40.848 --> 25:43.195
ANY BLEEDING
FROM YOUR NOSE OR GUMS?

25:43.265 --> 25:45.958
NO. IS THAT GOING
TO START HAPPENING?

25:46.959 --> 25:49.133
LOOK, I KNOW
THIS IS... UNFAIR,

25:49.201 --> 25:52.343
GIVEN ALL YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH
IN THE LAST COUPLE OF YEARS.

25:52.412 --> 25:54.897
OH, YOU--
YOU TALK ABOUT THAT

25:54.967 --> 25:56.761
LIKE YOU HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT,

25:56.830 --> 25:58.142
LIKE YOU WEREN'T
THERE WITH HIM

25:58.211 --> 26:00.523
BEHIND THE WHEEL
WHEN HE DIED.

26:00.593 --> 26:03.077
YOU KNOW WHAT?
NOTHING I CAN SAY TO YOU

26:03.146 --> 26:05.148
IS GOING TO CHANGE
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT ME.

26:05.218 --> 26:08.117
CLEARLY YOU'VE DECIDED
THAT I'M THIS VILLAIN

26:08.186 --> 26:10.326
AND YOUR FATHER IS A SAINT
AND THAT'S UP TO YOU.

26:10.395 --> 26:12.811
BUT YOU'VE JUST GOT TO PUT
THAT ON HOLD RIGHT NOW.

26:12.881 --> 26:16.021
LET ME SAVE YOUR LIFE
AND THEN YOU CAN GO BACK
TO HATING ME.

26:17.126 --> 26:19.887
I HAVEN'T EVEN
TOLD MY MOM YET.

26:19.957 --> 26:21.787
CAN WE JUST WAIT
UNTIL I TALK TO HER?

26:21.855 --> 26:23.651
I'LL DO IT TONIGHT.

26:23.720 --> 26:25.894
- PLEASE JUST KEEP THIS
BETWEEN US FOR NOW, OKAY?
- APRIL--

26:25.962 --> 26:28.068
SOONER OR LATER PEOPLE
ARE GOING TO FIND OUT
ABOUT THIS.

26:28.137 --> 26:30.001
YOU CAN'T KEEP SOMETHING
LIKE THIS SECRET.

26:30.070 --> 26:33.315
AND ANOTHER THING,
YOU CANNOT BLOW ME OFF
THE WAY YOU DID...

26:33.384 --> 26:36.422
LAST NIGHT.
FROM NOW ON WHEN I CALL YOU

26:36.490 --> 26:38.492
- YOU'VE GOT
TO PICK UP THE PHONE.
- OKAY.

26:38.561 --> 26:41.082
OKAY, GEORGE, I WILL.

26:46.051 --> 26:48.986
I KNOW OUR RELATIONSHIP
IS-IS-- IS COMPLICATED,

26:49.055 --> 26:51.402
BUT...

26:51.471 --> 26:53.094
I STILL LOVE YOU.

27:01.204 --> 27:04.105
Girl:
SO IF WE COULD MOVE THIS
OVER THERE AND THAT...

27:06.589 --> 27:09.144
BRENNA, DO YOU NEED A TASK?

27:09.212 --> 27:10.973
THE SOUP IS OUT.

27:11.042 --> 27:12.941
ISN'T THAT, LIKE,
THE ONE TASK?

27:13.009 --> 27:16.220
- YOU CAN'T JUST SIGN IN
AND THEN LEAVE AGAIN.
- WHY DO YOU CARE?

27:16.288 --> 27:18.188
BECAUSE I'M THE PRESIDENT
OF THIS CLUB

27:18.257 --> 27:20.880
AND IF OUR ADVISOR FINDS OUT
THAT I'M LETTING YOU LEAVE--

27:20.949 --> 27:23.779
WELL, THEN DON'T TELL HIM.
CHELSEA, COME ON.

27:23.848 --> 27:25.678
ACTUALLY I THINK
I'M GONNA STAY.

27:25.747 --> 27:27.403
SERIOUSLY?

27:27.472 --> 27:29.958
I'M, LIKE,
STARTING TO THINK ABOUT
COLLEGE APPLICATIONS--

27:30.027 --> 27:32.028
BECAUSE SOME PEOPLE
CARE ABOUT THEIR FUTURES.

27:32.097 --> 27:33.721
[ honks ]

27:33.789 --> 27:35.999
WHATEVER.

27:36.067 --> 27:38.069
I DON'T LIVE
FOR THE FUTURE.

27:38.138 --> 27:41.003
WE COULD ALL DIE TOMORROW.
GOTTA HAVE FUN WHILE YOU CAN.

27:45.422 --> 27:47.355
This is Sara Carver's
voicemail.

27:47.423 --> 27:49.252
I'll get right back to you.
[ beeps ]

27:49.322 --> 27:51.945
HEY, MOM, IT'S ME.
I WAS JUST WONDERING
IF YOU'RE HOME YET.

27:52.015 --> 27:53.602
I'M LEAVING WORK
A LITTLE EARLY

27:53.672 --> 27:56.328
AND I HAVE TO TELL YOU
SOMETHING.

27:57.433 --> 27:59.021
OKAY, SEE YOU SOON!

27:59.090 --> 28:01.093
HEY, SORRY I WAS
WEIRD EARLIER.

28:01.162 --> 28:03.128
- IT WAS A CRAZY MORNING.
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

28:11.067 --> 28:13.000
- LEAVING EARLY?
- YEAH.

28:13.069 --> 28:15.244
YOUR FLU IS THE GIFT
THAT KEEPS ON GIVING.

28:15.314 --> 28:17.178
- I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.
- COOL.

28:17.247 --> 28:18.868
I'LL PROBABLY STILL
BE HERE FROM TODAY.

28:18.938 --> 28:21.458
I WANT LAWRENCE TO SEE
I'M NOT AFRAID TO PULL
AN ALL-NIGHTER.

28:23.597 --> 28:27.429
HEY, APRIL, LAWRENCE WANTS
TO SEE YOU AS SOON AS HE
GETS OFF THIS CALL.

28:27.498 --> 28:30.086
- YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S ABOUT?
- [ IM chiming ]

28:34.125 --> 28:35.022
NO.

28:53.731 --> 28:55.836
YOU'RE NOT
TOTALLY ILLITERATE.

28:55.905 --> 28:58.115
THANK YOU.

28:58.183 --> 29:00.358
BUT I CAN'T RUN YOUR STORY
EVEN IF I WANTED TO.

29:00.428 --> 29:03.119
MARK HAS A QUOTA
OF STORIES HE NEEDS
TO FILL FOR HIS CONTRACT.

29:03.189 --> 29:06.537
OKAY. UH, WELL,
THANKS FOR READING IT.

29:07.987 --> 29:09.333
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

29:09.402 --> 29:11.957
I'M SORRY.
I THOUGHT THAT WAS IT.

29:12.026 --> 29:14.960
NO. I'VE GOT A QUESTION
FOR YOU. SIT.

29:15.028 --> 29:18.031
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT BRUCE HENDRIE?

29:18.101 --> 29:20.275
THE REAL-ESTATE DEVELOPER?

29:20.344 --> 29:22.036
YOU HEAR HE'S RUNNING
FOR GOVERNOR IN THE NEXT TERM?

29:22.105 --> 29:23.933
- I-- I--
- DON'T LIE.

29:24.002 --> 29:26.557
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE ANY WAY
OF KNOWING UNLESS YOU KNOW
HIS HOUSEKEEPER

29:26.625 --> 29:29.422
WHO TOLD MY HOUSEKEEPER--
AND YES, HIS HOUSEKEEPER
IS LEGAL,

29:29.490 --> 29:31.492
SO DON'T BOTHER STARTING
WITH THAT ANGLE.

29:31.561 --> 29:34.393
- I'M SORRY, EXCUSE ME?
- KEEP UP.

29:34.461 --> 29:37.291
I'M GIVING YOU
AN ASSIGNMENT.

29:37.361 --> 29:39.328
I WANT YOU
TO PROFILE THIS GUY.

29:39.397 --> 29:41.710
CRAIG WAS SUPPOSED TO DO IT,
BUT HE JUST GAVE HIS
TWO WEEKS' NOTICE.

29:41.779 --> 29:44.057
HE'S GOING TO WORK
FOR THE "TIMES."

29:44.126 --> 29:48.337
IT PAINS ME TO SAY THIS,
BECAUSE I THINK EACH GENERATION
GETS MORE AND MORE VAPID,

29:48.406 --> 29:51.202
BUT IT'S CLEAR THAT YOUTH
IS THE FUTURE OF POLITICS.

29:51.271 --> 29:54.964
EVERY PIECE OF NEWS SEEMS
TO LIVE AND DIE ON FACEBOOK,

29:55.034 --> 29:57.001
- TWITTER, YOUTUBE.
- I HAVE THOSE.

29:57.070 --> 29:59.589
CONGRATULATIONS.
SO YOU UP FOR IT?

29:59.659 --> 30:03.386
YEAH!
YES, OF COURSE.

30:03.455 --> 30:06.251
GOOD.
I'LL CALL PAM IN H.R.

30:06.320 --> 30:07.978
[ clicks ]

30:08.047 --> 30:10.325
[ nasal voice ]
Human Resources,
this is Pam.

30:10.394 --> 30:12.568
I NEED YOU TO SET UP
A NEW EXPENSE ACCOUNT

30:12.637 --> 30:15.260
FOR... APRIL CARVER, RIGHT?

30:19.540 --> 30:22.544
♪ HAPPY YOU'RE MY "G,"
YOU KNOW I OWN THIS TOWN ♪

30:22.613 --> 30:25.064
♪ You know it's on
whenever I come around ♪

30:25.133 --> 30:28.516
♪ Representing all the way
from London town... ♪

30:28.585 --> 30:30.518
- TEQUILA?
- WHAT ARE YOU
CHASING IT WITH?

30:30.586 --> 30:32.415
TEQUILA.

30:38.663 --> 30:41.322
- [ coughs ]
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

30:41.391 --> 30:45.015
- YEAH, I'M GREAT.
- COME HERE. LET ME SHOW YOU
THE REST OF THE HOUSE.

30:57.337 --> 30:59.305
THIS IS TYLER.
HE CRASHES HERE.

30:59.374 --> 31:02.031
TYLER, THIS IS BRENNA.
SHE GOES TO CHARTON.

31:03.516 --> 31:05.586
HEY, SEAN.

31:13.181 --> 31:15.459
TAKE CARE OF MY MAN TY,
ALL RIGHT?

31:15.528 --> 31:17.323
WAIT, SEAN.

31:18.530 --> 31:20.361
WHAT'S WRONG?

31:20.430 --> 31:23.605
- NOTHING.
- THEN WHY ARE YOU,
LIKE, SHAKING?

31:23.673 --> 31:28.057
- I'M NOT.
- OH RIGHT!

31:28.126 --> 31:30.440
YOU'RE A PRIVATE-SCHOOL
GIRL.

31:30.509 --> 31:32.751
YOU PROBABLY ONLY SPREAD
YOUR LEGS FOR YOUR HORSE.

31:32.820 --> 31:34.547
[ snickers ]

31:50.597 --> 31:53.221
- GUESS WHAT I'M DOING TONIGHT?
- UH...

31:53.289 --> 31:56.396
- WHAT?
- GOING ON MY FIRST
INTERNET DATE!

31:59.261 --> 32:01.608
- THAT WAS FAST.
- [ laughs ] YEAH.

32:01.678 --> 32:04.991
THANKS TO YOU.
YOU KNOW THAT MAN
YOU FOUND ME?

32:05.060 --> 32:09.029
MY 79% MATCH?
HE SUGGESTED THAT WE JUST
CUT TO THE CHASE

32:09.098 --> 32:12.275
AND MEET UP.
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
I FIGURED "WHY NOT?"

32:15.623 --> 32:17.693
OH NO,

32:17.762 --> 32:21.422
- IS THAT CRAZY?
- NO NO! MOM, THAT'S AWESOME.

32:21.490 --> 32:23.182
LET ME DO YOUR EYES.
COME.

32:23.250 --> 32:25.391
[ sighs ]
OH.

32:25.460 --> 32:27.634
HEY, WHAT DID YOU
WANT TO TELL ME?
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

32:27.703 --> 32:30.603
OH, UM...

32:30.672 --> 32:33.054
I GOT MY FIRST
BIG ASSIGNMENT
FROM LAWRENCE TODAY.

32:33.123 --> 32:35.746
- REALLY?!
- MOM, YOU HAVE TO KEEP
YOUR EYES CLOSED.

32:35.815 --> 32:38.508
OH, APRIL,
I'M SO EXCITED!

32:38.576 --> 32:42.269
I CAN'T WAIT TO BRAG
ABOUT YOU ON MY DATE!

32:42.338 --> 32:46.377
[ giggles ]
I'M SO GLAD I PICKED UP
THIS PURPLE EYE SHADOW.

32:46.447 --> 32:48.759
I JUST FELT LIKE I NEEDED
A LITTLE EXTRA SOMETHING.

32:48.827 --> 32:50.657
I WANTED SOMETHING
PLAYFUL,

32:50.727 --> 32:54.109
BUT NOT
JUVENILE PLAYFUL, RIGHT?
IT'S AGE-APPROPRIATE.

32:54.179 --> 32:57.146
I GUESS-- YOU KNOW WHAT?
A BETTER WORD FOR IT
IS "SPIRITED."

32:57.215 --> 32:59.701
- SPIRITED, I FEEL LIKE--
- MOM.

32:59.769 --> 33:03.394
WHAT'S WRONG?
YOU'RE NOT FINISHING
YOUR SENTENCES AGAIN.

33:03.463 --> 33:05.568
I'M NERVOUS.

33:05.637 --> 33:08.641
I HAVEN'T BEEN
ON A DATE IN 25 YEARS.

33:08.710 --> 33:12.541
AND NOW, WHAT AM I?
I'M MAKING MYSELF LOOK PRETTY
TO GO MEET A COMPLETE STRANGER.

33:12.611 --> 33:14.682
I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE I'M JUST
TOO OLD FOR THIS.

33:14.750 --> 33:17.478
STOP. ANY MAN WOULD BE
LUCKY TO MEET YOU.

33:17.547 --> 33:19.825
LOOK AT YOU,
YOU'RE HOT.

33:19.894 --> 33:21.481
[ laughs ]
YEAH.

33:23.138 --> 33:25.210
YOU CAN DO THIS.

33:25.278 --> 33:27.384
YOU DESERVE
TO MEET SOMEONE.

33:30.836 --> 33:35.220
- WHO'S THE THERAPIST HERE?
- SOMETIMES I DON'T KNOW.

33:36.669 --> 33:39.464
- NOW TAKE OFF THE CAPE.
- IT'S A PONCHO.

33:39.534 --> 33:41.881
OH OKAY.
TAKE OFF THE PONCHO.

33:41.950 --> 33:45.436
IT'S--
IT'S FROM NEPAL.

33:45.506 --> 33:47.369
DON'T TAKE THIS
THE WRONG WAY,

33:47.439 --> 33:49.302
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
IT BELONGS ON A DONKEY.

33:50.200 --> 33:51.683
REALLY?

33:51.752 --> 33:53.616
OH MY GOD.

34:14.431 --> 34:16.329
[ phone rings, beeps ]

34:16.398 --> 34:19.574
- HEY.
- THERE YOU ARE!
I THOUGHT YOU DIED.

34:19.643 --> 34:21.748
- WHAT?
- It's been, like, 24 hours

34:21.818 --> 34:23.820
AND YOU STILL HAVEN'T TOLD ME
ABOUT YOUR DATE WITH DOMINIC.

34:23.889 --> 34:26.409
- I THOUGHT HE KILLED YOU.
- OH YEAH, UM,

34:26.478 --> 34:29.101
SORRY, IT'S JUST BEEN
ONE OF THOSE DAYS.

34:29.170 --> 34:31.275
ACTUALLY...

34:31.344 --> 34:33.242
I NEED
TO TALK TO YOU.

34:33.311 --> 34:35.865
WELL, COME GET A DRINK
WITH ME AT THE PALACE.
I HAD A CRAP DAY, TOO.

34:35.934 --> 34:38.835
MY PART-TIMER QUIT
SO I'M WORKING DOUBLE SHIFTS
FOR THE REST OF THE WEEK.

34:38.903 --> 34:41.181
How much
does my life suck?

34:41.251 --> 34:43.909
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T REALLY FEEL
LIKE GOING TO A BAR.

34:43.978 --> 34:46.601
DO YOU THINK MAYBE
THERE'S SOMEWHERE QUIET
WHERE WE CAN TALK?

34:46.670 --> 34:48.224
- [ siren blares ]
- WAIT, WHAT?!

34:48.293 --> 34:50.190
NEVER MIND.

34:50.260 --> 34:51.882
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.

34:53.505 --> 34:55.195
♪ WHILE THE PEOPLE SLEEP ♪

34:55.264 --> 34:57.335
♪ I LIE AWAKE ♪

34:57.405 --> 34:59.579
♪ ENCASED IN DREAMS
THAT CARRY ME ♪

34:59.648 --> 35:02.514
♪ TO A DISTANT SOUND ♪

35:02.583 --> 35:05.827
♪ TO UNDERTAKE,
I FEEL ITS WEIGHT ♪

35:05.896 --> 35:08.313
♪ EVEN THOUGH I ♪

35:08.382 --> 35:11.523
♪ AM HELPLESS OF ♪

35:11.592 --> 35:15.320
- ♪ THE FORCE. ♪
- [ dance music playing ]

35:17.045 --> 35:19.565
OH MY GOD,
I'M ALREADY DRUNK.
YOU HAVE TO CATCH UP.

35:19.634 --> 35:22.775
HERE, I GOT YOU
A VODKA... SOMETHING.

35:22.844 --> 35:24.398
TONIC.

35:26.778 --> 35:28.885
OH, THIS IS GARY.
HE'S BEEN KEEPING ME COMPANY.

35:28.954 --> 35:30.679
GARY, THIS IS
MY BEST FRIEND APRIL.

35:30.748 --> 35:32.784
HI.

35:32.853 --> 35:35.409
[ sighs ]
YEAH, HE DOESN'T
TALK MUCH.

35:35.478 --> 35:37.376
IT'S OKAY.
COME ON, LET'S PICK
SOME SONGS.

35:37.445 --> 35:39.653
SORRY, I DON'T THINK
THEY HAVE ANY COUNTRY.

35:41.793 --> 35:43.001
SO WHAT'S UP?

35:43.070 --> 35:45.315
YOU SEEM BUMMED.
IS IT THE BOY?

35:46.798 --> 35:48.318
YEAH, UH...

35:48.387 --> 35:51.251
WE HAD AN AWESOME DATE
LAST NIGHT AND HE KIND OF
BLEW ME OFF TODAY.

35:51.320 --> 35:54.565
SEE, THIS IS THE PROBLEM
WITH GUYS LIKE DOMINIC.
THEY'RE TOO PASSIVE.

35:54.635 --> 35:56.429
IT MIGHT HAVE BEEN
MY FAULT THOUGH.

35:56.498 --> 35:57.983
I SAW HIM
THIS MORNING AND IT
WAS REALLY AWKWARD--

35:58.052 --> 36:01.365
STOP IT.
DON'T DO THAT GIRL THING
WHERE YOU BLAME YOURSELF.

36:01.434 --> 36:03.608
- I'M NOT, I JUST--
- YOU JUST NEED A REBOUND.

36:03.677 --> 36:05.956
SO YOU KNOW, LIKE,
PICK A GUY, ANY GUY.

36:06.025 --> 36:08.682
- I'LL MAKE IT HAPPEN FOR YOU.
- UGH, NO, I'M OKAY.

36:08.751 --> 36:10.547
OKAY, WELL, IF YOU
CHANGE YOUR MIND,

36:10.615 --> 36:12.929
COME DANCE WITH ME.
GUYS LOVE LESBIANS.

36:14.481 --> 36:16.518
♪ Baby girl, I never,
I never ♪

36:16.588 --> 36:19.106
♪ I never wanna be the one ♪

36:19.177 --> 36:20.385
♪ To take your hand and say ♪

36:20.454 --> 36:21.972
♪ I'll always be the one ♪

36:22.041 --> 36:24.389
♪ To take your breath away,
I wanna be the man ♪

36:24.458 --> 36:26.010
♪ To make you
feel it, girl ♪

36:26.079 --> 36:28.461
♪ I wanna, I wanna,
I wanna ♪

36:28.530 --> 36:32.327
♪ One in a million, baby ♪

36:32.396 --> 36:33.673
♪ Now you be here... ♪

36:33.742 --> 36:36.608
- [ water running ]
- [ sniffs ]

36:38.505 --> 36:40.059
YOU WERE PARTYING?

36:40.128 --> 36:42.786
- WHAT?
- I HAVE CASH.

36:42.855 --> 36:47.101
OH UH, NO.
THIS ISN'T FROM THAT.

36:47.170 --> 36:49.931
FINE.
DON'T SHARE.

36:52.831 --> 36:55.764
♪ Dance like
it's the last song ♪

36:55.833 --> 36:59.043
♪ Move it till
your body hurts, baby ♪

36:59.112 --> 37:02.875
♪ We can make
this work, dance like
it's the last song... ♪

37:02.943 --> 37:06.396
- BETH!
- WHATEVER, I CAN BE A FEMINIST
AND STILL LIKE THIS MUSIC.

37:06.465 --> 37:08.121
- OKAY?
- NO. DOMINIC'S HERE.

37:08.190 --> 37:10.262
- WHERE?
- RIGHT THERE.

37:11.090 --> 37:14.059
OKAY, HE'S WAY HOTTER
THAN HIS PROFILE PICTURE.

37:14.128 --> 37:16.648
AND HE'S LOOKING
OVER HERE.

37:19.063 --> 37:22.032
- OUCH!
- SEE? HE'S OVER IT ALREADY.

37:22.101 --> 37:26.898
- I'M JUST GONNA LET IT GO.
- OKAY, BUT IF YOU DON'T
CONFRONT HIM RIGHT NOW,

37:26.967 --> 37:29.902
YOU ARE NOT ALLOWED
TO OBSESS TO ME LATER
ABOUT WHAT WENT WRONG,

37:29.971 --> 37:33.561
BECAUSE YOU HAVE A WINDOW
RIGHT THIS MINUTE TO FIND OUT
FROM THE SOURCE.

37:33.630 --> 37:35.701
LIKE, WHAT DO YOU
HAVE TO LOSE?

37:42.708 --> 37:44.503
OKAY, WHAT'S UP WITH YOU?

37:44.572 --> 37:47.989
- HEY, I DIDN'T SEE YOU.
- WHATEVER. YEAH, YOU DID.

37:48.057 --> 37:50.474
WHY ARE YOU BEING WEIRD?
WE HAD A GREAT TIME
LAST NIGHT.

37:50.543 --> 37:53.340
IS THIS JUST HOW
YOU ARE WITH GIRLS?

37:53.409 --> 37:55.065
HI, I'M APRIL.

37:59.655 --> 38:02.487
LOOK, WHATEVER
IT IS, JUST TELL ME.
I HATE DRAMA.

38:02.556 --> 38:04.730
REALLY?
THAT'S KIND OF IRONIC.

38:04.798 --> 38:07.456
- WHY?
- I SAW YOU TALKING
TO THAT GEORGE GUY TODAY.

38:09.114 --> 38:10.735
YOU DID?

38:12.635 --> 38:14.360
WHAT DID--
WHAT DID YOU HEAR?

38:14.429 --> 38:17.086
THAT YOU CAN'T TELL ANYONE
YOU'RE SEEING HIM
AND HE LOVES YOU.

38:17.155 --> 38:19.054
- HE'S THE GUY WHO CALLED YOU
LAST NIGHT, RIGHT?
- OH NO, HE'S NOT--

38:19.123 --> 38:21.090
IT'S COOL.
WHAT IS HE, LIKE, MARRIED?

38:21.159 --> 38:23.472
AND YOU'RE WAITING
FOR HIM TO LEAVE HIS WIFE
OR SOMETHING?

38:23.541 --> 38:25.923
- 'CAUSE THAT'S KINDA
THE DEFINITION OF DRAMA.
- DOMINIC, HE'S MY UNCLE.

38:25.992 --> 38:28.512
- WAIT.
- GEORGE IS MY UNCLE.

38:28.581 --> 38:31.860
IT'S A SECRET THAT
I SAW HIM, BECAUSE EVERYONE
IN MY FAMILY HATES HIM,

38:31.929 --> 38:34.518
WHICH IS A WHOLE LONG STORY.
BUT THAT'S WHO HE IS.

38:34.588 --> 38:38.143
- SO NO SECRET BOYFRIEND.
- NO.

38:38.211 --> 38:40.835
- YOU'RE JUST SLEEPING
WITH YOUR UNCLE.
- YES.

38:40.903 --> 38:42.664
- THEN THAT'S FINE.
- [ laughs ]

38:44.666 --> 38:46.702
CAN WE JUST REWIND

38:46.771 --> 38:48.601
AND PRETEND
IT'S LAST NIGHT AGAIN?

38:51.052 --> 38:52.639
OKAY.

38:55.228 --> 38:57.610
[ phone vibrating ]

38:57.679 --> 38:59.059
ONE SEC.

39:00.199 --> 39:02.201
UGH, IT'S MY
LITTLE SISTER.

39:02.269 --> 39:04.963
- BREN?
- [ crying ] APRIL.

39:05.032 --> 39:06.998
BREN, WHERE ARE YOU?
ARE YOU OKAY?

39:07.068 --> 39:08.967
- NO.
- [ people laughing ]

39:09.036 --> 39:10.934
STAY ON THE PHONE.
I'M ON MY WAY.

39:12.003 --> 39:13.074
I'M SORRY.

39:16.630 --> 39:19.873
HEY, SEXY,
I SAVED YOU A SEAT.

39:20.358 --> 39:22.532
YEAH, KEEP DOING THAT.
GIRLS LOVE THAT.

39:22.601 --> 39:24.500
[ laughing ]

39:24.568 --> 39:26.985
[ camera clicking ]

39:28.365 --> 39:30.436
DUDE, LOOK,
SHE'S SALUTING US!

39:30.505 --> 39:32.092
HELP ME CAPTION THIS.

39:35.096 --> 39:36.650
- HEY.
- [ beeps, clatters ]

39:36.719 --> 39:38.789
BREN, LET'S GO.

39:38.858 --> 39:40.481
COME ON.

39:40.550 --> 39:42.655
[ grunts ]
MOVE!

39:43.588 --> 39:46.693
[ retches, coughs ]

39:47.833 --> 39:50.041
[ slurring ]
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

39:50.110 --> 39:53.010
I PROMISE I'LL NEVER
LIE TO YOU AGAIN.

39:53.079 --> 39:54.771
[ sighs ]

39:56.221 --> 39:58.637
PLEASE DON'T TELL MOM.

39:58.706 --> 40:00.811
SHE'LL FREAK OUT.

40:01.847 --> 40:03.539
I WON'T.

40:03.608 --> 40:04.918
THANKS, APE.

40:04.987 --> 40:07.543
I'M SO GLAD YOU
STILL LIVE WITH US.

40:07.612 --> 40:09.130
IF YOU DIDN'T I...

40:10.510 --> 40:11.856
I WOULD DIE.

40:20.728 --> 40:22.730
[ soft laughter,
conversation ]

40:38.952 --> 40:41.577
I'M SORRY,
I WASN'T TRYING TO SPY
ON YOU OR ANYTHING.

40:41.646 --> 40:43.958
- NO NO NO, I'M THE ONE
WHO SHOULD APOLOGIZE.
- I JUST--

40:44.027 --> 40:46.304
PLEASE, NO DAUGHTER
WANTS TO WATCH HER MOTHER
DOING THAT.

40:46.373 --> 40:49.032
NOT THAT THERE'S
ANYTHING WRONG WITH IT.
IT'S NATURAL,

40:49.101 --> 40:51.137
- BUT I JUST--
- MOM, IT'S FINE.

40:51.206 --> 40:54.831
OKAY, SO FIRST HE TOOK ME
TO AN INCREDIBLE FLAMENCO
PERFORMANCE--

40:54.900 --> 40:57.005
THIS ARGENTINEAN WOMAN,
IRINA SOMETHING--

40:57.074 --> 40:59.594
AND THEN WE WENT
TO HARVARD SQUARE FOR DESSERT

40:59.664 --> 41:01.320
AND TALKED
UNTIL THE CAFE CLOSED.

41:01.389 --> 41:03.668
AND IT WAS JUST--
I DON'T REMEMBER

41:03.737 --> 41:05.876
BEING THIS HAPPY.

41:07.947 --> 41:09.639
IS SOMETHING
WRONG, HONEY?

41:10.744 --> 41:14.056
YEAH, I'M JUST--
I'M TIRED.

41:15.161 --> 41:17.128
OH, WHY DON'T YOU
GET SOME SLEEP?

41:17.197 --> 41:19.373
YOU KNOW, MAYBE YOU
SHOULD SKIP THE TEA.

41:19.442 --> 41:21.719
THEY ALWAYS SAY
IT'S CAFFEINE-FREE,
BUT I DON'T BELIEVE THEM.

41:21.789 --> 41:23.894
COME ON, YOU GO TO BED.

41:26.414 --> 41:28.451
THANK YOU FOR TONIGHT.

41:29.313 --> 41:31.246
I NEVER COULD HAVE
DONE IT WITHOUT YOU.

41:45.123 --> 41:47.193
[ sobs ]

41:52.786 --> 41:55.271
[ sobbing ]

41:58.929 --> 42:01.001
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DAD.

42:02.380 --> 42:05.280
SO I'VE GOT SOME
PRETTY BIG NEWS.

42:06.731 --> 42:08.664
I GOT PROMOTED.

42:08.733 --> 42:11.045
JUST KIDDING.

42:12.875 --> 42:15.393
I MEANT
MY OTHER NEWS.

42:15.463 --> 42:18.121
MAYBE YOU
ALREADY KNOW.

42:18.190 --> 42:20.295
I DON'T KNOW HOW--
HOW THIS ALL WORKS.

42:20.364 --> 42:22.297
[ sobs ]

42:22.367 --> 42:24.126
OHH.

42:27.302 --> 42:29.443
ANYWAY.

42:29.512 --> 42:31.996
SO IT LOOKS LIKE
I MIGHT BE

42:32.065 --> 42:35.206
SEEING YOU
SOMETIME SOON.

42:37.001 --> 42:40.074
AND... DON'T TAKE THIS
THE WRONG WAY...

42:40.143 --> 42:41.282
[ sniffs ]

42:44.458 --> 42:46.735
[ exhales ]
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO WAIT AWHILE.

42:49.358 --> 42:51.257
I'M NOT READY YET.

42:59.853 --> 43:01.336
- HEY.
- HI.

43:01.405 --> 43:03.027
THOSE ARE
REALLY PRETTY.

43:03.097 --> 43:05.099
THANKS.
THEY'RE FOR MY DAD.

43:17.353 --> 43:18.664
[ huffs ]
